public class CoordinateMap<V>
extends java.util.TreeMap<Coordinate,V>

Represents an ordered mapping of Coordinate object keys into a parameterized type values. This class extends TreeMap, so iterators over the coordinate keys managed by the map will be returned in left-to-right, top-down order. Convenience methods of this class give uses of class the ability to address values by (x,y) coordinate pairs without requiring the user to create a new Coordinate object.

Author:
Eric Peterson
